# Frontend accessibility guard

Apply when changing **UI components, styles, or interaction behavior** in the client.

**Docs:** `docs/styleguide/ui-styleguide.md`, `docs/styleguide/frontend-patterns.md`.

## Checks

- Forms: associated labels, error text, and focus management after submit/errors.
- Interactive elements: keyboard operability where applicable.
- Contrast and text sizing remain readable on touched views.
- Touch targets remain usable on small screens.

## Style consistency

- Prefer Tailwind utilities; avoid large one-off CSS unless tokenized in **`index.css`**.
- Feature UI under **`client/src/features/*`**; keep pages as orchestrators when possible.

## Pre-commit

- Update styleguide or component docs when UX conventions change materially.
